# PYETUN - README FILE # 
Author: Luis "Drune" Marques


-----------------------------------------
To install:		
-----------------------------------------
As root:
* python setup.py install

Run with:
* pyetun ( or /usr/bin/pyetun )

Note: Edit pyetun.conf to fit your needs ;)
Enjoy.

-------------------------------------------
Configuration: pyetun.conf
------------------------------------------

* There's a file with configuration options: pyetun.conf

* You can change your enlightenment_remote path, if you dont know where is it, use "whereis enlightenment_remote" or "find -name / enlightenment_remote".

Example (Default on Gentoo using Ebuilds):
	[paths]
	enlightement_remote="/usr/bin/enlightenment_remote"

* You can also change modules (normal+extra) path. Check the example:
Example:
	[modules]
	normal=/usr/lib/enlightenment/modules/
	extra=/usr/lib/enlightenment/modules_extra/

